article.headline: Liberty 103, VMI 88
article.story: LYNCHBURG, Va. (AP) -- Anthony Smith scored 30 points Tuesday night and Liberty beat VMI 103-88 in the first round of the Big South tournament. Reggie Williams matched Smith with 30 points for VMI (14-15), who led only briefly in the first half. Twins Chavis and Travis Holmes combined for 13 points in the last 3:35 of the first half to put VMI ahead 47-46. Alex McLean's layup reclaimed the lead for the Flames (16-15). Travis Holmes, who scored 19 points, made a pair of free throws to close the gap early in the second half, but Liberty built the lead to 65-55 with 11:18 to go on a jumper by TeeJay Bannister. Chavis Holmes had 26 points for VMI. Kyle Ohman scored 21 and B.J. Jenkins had 18 for Liberty.
